  "prompt": "What guidelines are in place regarding passport photos in Canada?",
  "response": "In Canada, passport photos must meet several specific guidelines:\n\n1. Size and Dimensions\n- 50mm x 70mm (2\" x 2.75\")\n- Head must be between 31mm and 36mm from chin to crown\n\n2. Characteristics\n- Taken within the last 6 months\n- Colored photo\n- Taken against a plain white or off-white background\n- Professionally taken\n- High resolution and clear\n\n3. Facial Requirements\n- Full front view facing the camera\n- Neutral facial expression\n- Eyes open and clearly visible\n- No accessories that obscure face\n- Glasses should not have tinted lenses or glare\n- No headwear except for religious or medical purposes\n\n4. Clothing\n- Normal everyday clothing\n- No uniforms\n- No overly busy patterns\n\n5. Technical Specifications\n- Printed on quality photo paper\n- No digital manipulations or alterations\n- Properly exposed and focused\n\n6. Additional Rules\n- Must be taken by a professional photographer familiar with passport photo requirements\n- Can be taken at many pharmacies, photo studios, and some government service centers\n\nThese guidelines ensure consistent, reliable identification documentation.",
